metadata.name: Skaldic Tales
metadata.description:
Eira, a solitary Viking shaman, ventures deep into the winter forest, guided by the whispers of the spirits. With each step, she listens to the crunch of the snow beneath her feet and the rustle of the wind through the trees, attuned to the subtle energies that surround her. Despite the harshness of the frozen landscape, Eira feels a sense of serenity and connection to the ancient forces that have always existed in these lands.  As she walks deeper into the woods, Eira embraces her role as a conduit between the human and spiritual worlds, carrying with her the wisdom and knowledge of her people, and the magic of the land itself.
